# A tech number has an even number of digits.
# If the number is split into two equal halves,
# then the square of the sum of these halves is equal to the number itself. 
# Write a program to generate and print all four-digit tech numbers.
n=1000
while n<=9999:
    s=str(n)
    s1=int(s[0:2])
    s2=int(s[2:4])
    su=s1+s2
    sq=su*su
    if sq==n:
        print(n)
    n+=1
